The paper deals with the development of machine learning methods for scene classification and change-point detection in video data, specifically body-worn video data from police departments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning methods such as convolutional neural networks and support vector machines suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as it deals with video data, and the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category, as it may have implications for the security and privacy of individuals captured in the video data. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as it deals with the identification of salient changes in large volumes of video data.
